cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the development of scale-equivariant convolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method in supervised learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of steerable filters and the development of a general theory for building scale-equivariant networks suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of the proposed models to previously developed methods, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
